        "content": "<p><strong>Complete Meal Components:</strong> Main + 2 Sides + Bread</p>\n<p><strong>Difficulty:</strong> Medium | <strong>Servings:</strong> 4 servings</p>\n<h3>Time Requirements</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Total Prep Time:</strong> 30 minutes</li>\n  <li><strong>Marination Time:</strong> 45 minutes vacuum (vs 12-24 hours)</li>\n  <li><strong>Cook Time:</strong> 15-20 minutes</li>\n  <li><strong>Total Time:</strong> 90 minutes</li>\n  <li><strong>Storage Duration:</strong> 1-2 years frozen</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Why This Meal is Special</h3>\n<h4>Yogurt Penetration:</h4>\n<p>Tandoori marinade is yogurt-based. Yogurt enzymes tenderize meat, but slowly. Vacuum sealing drives these enzymes deep into cuts made in the chicken, reducing marination time from 24 hours to 45 minutes.</p>\n<h3>COMPONENT 1: Vacuum Tandoori Chicken</h3>\n<h4>Ingredients:</h4>\n<ul>\n  <li>4 chicken legs (drumstick + thigh) or 4 breasts</li>\n  <li><strong>Marinade:</strong></li>\n  <li>1 cup plain yogurt</li>\n  <li>2 tbsp lemon juice</li>\n  <li>2 tbsp tandoori masala spice blend</li>\n  <li>1 tbsp ginger-garlic paste</li>\n  <li>1 tsp salt</li>\n  <li>1 tsp kashmiri chili powder (for color)</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Instructions:</h4>\n<ol>\n  <li><strong>Score:</strong> Make deep slashes in chicken meat (2-3 per piece). This helps marinade enter.</li>\n  <li><strong>Mix:</strong> Whisk all marinade ingredients.</li>\n  <li><strong>Coat:</strong> Rub marinade into chicken, specifically into the cuts.</li>\n  <li><strong>Vacuum Seal:</strong> Place in bag. Pulse seal (liquid).</li>\n  <li><strong>Marinate:</strong> 45 mins room temp or freeze.</li>\n</ol>\n<h4>Cooking:</h4>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Oven:</strong> 425F (220C) for 25-30 mins. Broil last 2 mins for char.</li>\n  <li><strong>Grill:</strong> Medium-high, 15-20 mins, turning often.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Storage:</h4>\n<ul>\n  <li>Freezer: 1-2 years</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>COMPONENT 2: Pre-Portioned Raita</h3>\n<h4>Ingredients:</h4>\n<ul>\n  <li>1 cup yogurt</li>\n  <li> cucumber, grated/squeezed</li>\n  <li> tsp cumin</li>\n  <li>Salt</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Instructions:</h4>\n<ol>\n  <li>Mix all ingredients.</li>\n  <li>Vacuum seal in small bags (Pulse).</li>\n  <li><strong>Store:</strong> Fridge 1 week. Freezing changes texture (separates), best fresh or fridge.</li>\n</ol>\n<h3>COMPONENT 3: Marinated Chickpea Salad</h3>\n<h4>Ingredients:</h4>\n<ul>\n  <li>1 can chickpeas, drained</li>\n  <li> red onion, diced</li>\n  <li>1 tomato, diced (add fresh)</li>\n  <li>1 tsp chaat masala</li>\n  <li>Lemon juice</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Instructions:</h4>\n<ol>\n  <li>Mix chickpeas, onion, spices. (Add tomato fresh later).</li>\n  <li>Vacuum seal.</li>\n  <li><strong>Store:</strong> Fridge 5 days.</li>\n</ol>\n<h3>COMPONENT 4: Frozen Naan</h3>\n<h4>Ingredients:</h4>\n<ul>\n  <li>Store-bought or homemade naan</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Instructions:</h4>\n<ol>\n  <li>Place parchment between naan.</li>\n  <li>Vacuum seal.</li>\n  <li><strong>Store:</strong> Freezer 6 months.</li>\n</ol>\n<h4>Reheating:</h4>\n<ul>\n  <li>Toaster or warm oven 2 mins.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>COMPLETE MEAL ASSEMBLY</h3>\n<h4>Timing:</h4>\n<ul>\n  <li>5:00 PM: Marinate chicken (45 min)</li>\n  <li>5:45 PM: Preheat oven</li>\n  <li>5:50 PM: Cook chicken</li>\n  <li>6:10 PM: Warm naan</li>\n  <li>6:15 PM: Serve with cold raita and salad</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Nutrition:</strong> ~480 calories, 35g protein, 15g fat, 45g carbs</p>\n"
