        "totalTime": "60 minutes",
        "content": "<p><strong>Complete Meal Components:</strong> Main + 3 Sides + Tortillas</p>\n<p><strong>Difficulty:</strong> Easy | <strong>Servings:</strong> 4 servings</p>\n<h3>Time Requirements</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Total Prep Time:</strong> 25 minutes</li>\n  <li><strong>Marination Time:</strong> 25 minutes vacuum</li>\n  <li><strong>Cook Time:</strong> 10 minutes</li>\n  <li><strong>Total Time:</strong> 60 minutes</li>\n  <li><strong>Storage Duration:</strong> 1-2 years frozen</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Why This Meal is Special</h3>\n<h4>Citrus Power:</h4>\n<p>Carne asada relies on lime/orange juice to tenderize skirt/flank steak. Too long (overnight) and the acid turns meat mushy. Too short (<1 hour) and it's tough. Vacuum sealing hits the sweet spot: 25 minutes under vacuum equals 4 hours traditional. Perfect texture, intense flavor.</p>\n<h3>COMPONENT 1: 25-Minute Carne Asada</h3>\n<h4>Ingredients:</h4>\n<ul>\n  <li>800g (1.75 lb) skirt steak or flank steak</li>\n  <li><strong>Marinade:</strong></li>\n  <li> cup orange juice</li>\n  <li> cup lime juice</li>\n  <li> cup soy sauce</li>\n  <li>4 cloves garlic, minced</li>\n  <li>1 tbsp chili powder</li>\n  <li>1 tsp cumin</li>\n  <li>1 tsp oregano</li>\n  <li> cup cilantro, chopped</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Instructions:</h4>\n<ol>\n  <li><strong>Mix:</strong> Combine all marinade ingredients.</li>\n  <li><strong>Seal:</strong> Place steak and marinade in bag. Pulse seal.</li>\n  <li><strong>Marinate:</strong> 25 minutes room temp. <strong>Do not exceed 45 mins</strong> or texture degrades. Freeze immediately if not cooking.</li>\n</ol>\n<h4>Cooking:</h4>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Grill:</strong> High heat, 3-4 mins per side (medium-rare).</li>\n  <li><strong>Rest:</strong> 5 mins. Slice against grain.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Storage:</h4>\n<ul>\n  <li>Freezer: 1-2 years</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>COMPONENT 2: Quick-Pickled Red Onions</h3>\n<h4>Ingredients:</h4>\n<ul>\n  <li>1 red onion, sliced thin</li>\n  <li> cup vinegar (apple cider or white)</li>\n  <li>1 tbsp sugar</li>\n  <li>1 tsp salt</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Instructions:</h4>\n<ol>\n  <li>Mix vinegar, sugar, salt.</li>\n  <li>Add onions to bag. Add liquid.</li>\n  <li>Pulse seal.</li>\n  <li><strong>Marinate:</strong> 15 mins. Ready to eat.</li>\n</ol>\n<h4>Storage:</h4>\n<ul>\n  <li>Fridge: 2 weeks.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>COMPONENT 3: Marinated Jalapeï¿½os</h3>\n<h4>Ingredients:</h4>\n<ul>\n  <li>4 jalapeï¿½os, sliced</li>\n  <li> cup soy sauce</li>\n  <li>1 tbsp lime juice</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Instructions:</h4>\n<ol>\n  <li>Combine in bag. Pulse seal.</li>\n  <li><strong>Marinate:</strong> 20 mins.</li>\n</ol>\n<h3>COMPONENT 4: Cilantro Lime Rice</h3>\n<h4>Ingredients:</h4>\n<ul>\n  <li>2 cups cooked white rice</li>\n  <li>Zest of 1 lime</li>\n  <li> cup cilantro (add fresh after reheating)</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Instructions:</h4>\n<ol>\n  <li>Cook rice. Cool.</li>\n  <li>Seal. Freeze.</li>\n  <li><strong>Reheat:</strong> Microwave. Stir in fresh lime juice/cilantro.</li>\n</ol>\n<h3>COMPONENT 5: Vacuum-Sealed Tortillas</h3>\n<h4>Instructions:</h4>\n<ol>\n  <li>Seal corn tortillas. Freeze.</li>\n  <li><strong>Reheat:</strong> Warm on skillet.</li>\n</ol>\n<h3>COMPLETE MEAL ASSEMBLY</h3>\n<h4>Timing:</h4>\n<ul>\n  <li>5:30 PM: Marinate steak (25 min)</li>\n  <li>5:30 PM: Pickle onions (15 min)</li>\n  <li>5:55 PM: Grill steak</li>\n  <li>6:00 PM: Reheat rice/tortillas</li>\n  <li>6:05 PM: Slice steak, serve</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Nutrition:</strong> ~500 calories, 30g protein, 20g fat, 50g carbs</p>\n"
