        "totalTime": "90 minutes",
        "content": "<p><strong>Complete Meal Components:</strong> Main + 2 Sides + Bread</p>\n<p><strong>Difficulty:</strong> Medium | <strong>Servings:</strong> 4-6 servings</p>\n<h3>Time Requirements</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Total Prep Time:</strong> 40 minutes</li>\n  <li><strong>Cook Time:</strong> 45 minutes (batch cook)</li>\n  <li><strong>Total Time:</strong> 90 minutes</li>\n  <li><strong>Storage Duration:</strong> 6-12 months frozen</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Why This Meal is Special</h3>\n<h4>Flavor Maturation:</h4>\n<p>Curries like Butter Chicken taste better the next day. Vacuum sealing freezes this \"next day\" flavor perfection for months. The spices continue to meld with the fats in the cream/butter even while frozen, resulting in a depth of flavor superior to fresh-cooked.</p>\n<h3>COMPONENT 1: Restaurant-Style Butter Chicken</h3>\n<h4>Ingredients:</h4>\n<ul>\n  <li>1kg chicken thighs, cubed</li>\n  <li><strong>Marinade:</strong> 1 cup yogurt, 1 tbsp ginger-garlic, spices</li>\n  <li><strong>Sauce:</strong> 1 can tomato puree, 1 cup cream, 100g butter, fenugreek leaves</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Instructions:</h4>\n<ol>\n  <li><strong>Cook:</strong> Make full butter chicken recipe (marinate chicken, sear, simmer in sauce).</li>\n  <li><strong>Cool:</strong> <strong>CRITICAL.</strong> Cool completely to room temp.</li>\n  <li><strong>Seal:</strong> Portion into bags. Pulse seal (liquid).</li>\n  <li><strong>Store:</strong> Freeze flat.</li>\n</ol>\n<h4>Reheating:</h4>\n<ul>\n  <li>Thaw. Simmer in pot 10 mins.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>COMPONENT 2: Pre-Made Saag (Spinach Curry)</h3>\n<h4>Ingredients:</h4>\n<ul>\n  <li>500g spinach, blanched/pureed</li>\n  <li>Onion, tomato, spices, cream</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Instructions:</h4>\n<ol>\n  <li><strong>Cook:</strong> Sautï¿½ aromatics, add spinach puree, simmer.</li>\n  <li><strong>Cool:</strong> Cool completely.</li>\n  <li><strong>Seal:</strong> Portion and seal.</li>\n  <li><strong>Store:</strong> Freeze flat.</li>\n</ol>\n<h3>COMPONENT 3: Garlic Naan (Pre-Buttered)</h3>\n<h4>Ingredients:</h4>\n<ul>\n  <li>Naan bread</li>\n  <li>Garlic butter</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Instructions:</h4>\n<ol>\n  <li>Spread garlic butter on naan.</li>\n  <li>Place parchment between slices.</li>\n  <li>Vacuum seal.</li>\n  <li><strong>Reheat:</strong> Oven 400F (200C) 3-4 mins.</li>\n</ol>\n<h3>COMPONENT 4: Basmati Rice</h3>\n<h4>Instructions:</h4>\n<ol>\n  <li>Cook basmati rice. Cool.</li>\n  <li>Seal flat. Freeze.</li>\n</ol>\n<h3>COMPLETE MEAL ASSEMBLY</h3>\n<h4>Timing:</h4>\n<ul>\n  <li>5:30 PM: Thaw curries/rice</li>\n  <li>5:45 PM: Reheat Butter Chicken and Saag (stovetop)</li>\n  <li>5:50 PM: Reheat rice (microwave)</li>\n  <li>5:55 PM: Warm naan in oven</li>\n  <li>6:00 PM: Serve</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Nutrition:</strong> ~700 calories, 40g protein, 35g fat, 60g carbs</p>\n"
