        "content": "<p><strong>Complete Meal Components:</strong> Main + Pasta + Side + Bread</p>\n<p><strong>Difficulty:</strong> Medium | <strong>Servings:</strong> 8-10 servings (Batch)</p>\n<h3>Time Requirements</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Total Prep Time:</strong> 30 minutes</li>\n  <li><strong>Cook Time:</strong> 6-8 hours (slow cook)</li>\n  <li><strong>Storage Duration:</strong> 6-12 months</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Why This Meal is Special</h3>\n<h4>Investment Cooking:</h4>\n<p>An 8-hour ragu is a labor of love. Vacuum sealing allows you to do this ONCE and enjoy it 10 times over the next year with zero degradation. No freezer burn, no ice crystals - just perfect, rich sauce on demand.</p>\n<h3>COMPONENT 1: Traditional Beef Ragu</h3>\n<h4>Ingredients:</h4>\n<ul>\n  <li>1.5kg beef chuck, cubed</li>\n  <li>Onions, carrots, celery, wine, tomatoes, herbs</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Instructions:</h4>\n<ol>\n  <li><strong>Cook:</strong> Braise beef in sauce for 6-8 hours until falling apart. Shred.</li>\n  <li><strong>Cool:</strong> Cool completely.</li>\n  <li><strong>Seal:</strong> Portion into 2-cup bags. Pulse seal.</li>\n  <li><strong>Store:</strong> Freeze flat.</li>\n</ol>\n<h3>COMPONENT 2: Fresh Pasta Portions</h3>\n<h4>Ingredients:</h4>\n<ul>\n  <li>Fresh pasta (store bought or homemade)</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Instructions:</h4>\n<ol>\n  <li>Dust with flour to prevent sticking.</li>\n  <li>Portion into bags.</li>\n  <li><strong>Gentle Seal:</strong> Don't crush.</li>\n  <li><strong>Store:</strong> Freeze 3-4 months. Cook from frozen.</li>\n</ol>\n<h3>COMPONENT 3: Parmesan Herb Butter</h3>\n<h4>Instructions:</h4>\n<ol>\n  <li>Mix butter, parmesan, herbs.</li>\n  <li>Roll into log. Seal.</li>\n  <li><strong>Use:</strong> Toss with hot pasta.</li>\n</ol>\n<h3>COMPONENT 4: Garlic Bread</h3>\n<h4>Instructions:</h4>\n<ol>\n  <li>Prep garlic bread.</li>\n  <li>Seal. Freeze.</li>\n</ol>\n<h3>COMPLETE MEAL ASSEMBLY</h3>\n<h4>Timing:</h4>\n<ul>\n  <li>5:30 PM: Thaw ragu</li>\n  <li>5:45 PM: Reheat ragu (simmer)</li>\n  <li>5:50 PM: Boil water, cook pasta</li>\n  <li>5:55 PM: Bake garlic bread</li>\n  <li>6:00 PM: Toss pasta with ragu/butter</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Nutrition:</strong> ~650 calories, 35g protein, 25g fat, 70g carbs</p>\n"
