        "content": "<p><strong>Complete Meal Components:</strong> Main + 2 Sides</p>\n<p><strong>Difficulty:</strong> Easy | <strong>Servings:</strong> 4 servings</p>\n<h3>Time Requirements</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Total Prep Time:</strong> 20 minutes</li>\n  <li><strong>Marination Time:</strong> 20 minutes vacuum</li>\n  <li><strong>Cook Time:</strong> 20 minutes</li>\n  <li><strong>Storage Duration:</strong> 1-2 years frozen</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Why This Meal is Special</h3>\n<h4>Herb Infusion:</h4>\n<p>Pork tenderloin is lean and can be bland. A vacuum herb rub penetrates the outer layer in 20 minutes, creating a flavor crust that seasons the meat internally as it cooks.</p>\n<h3>COMPONENT 1: Quick-Marinated Pork Tenderloin</h3>\n<h4>Ingredients:</h4>\n<ul>\n  <li>2 pork tenderloins</li>\n  <li><strong>Rub:</strong> Rosemary, thyme, garlic, olive oil, mustard</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Instructions:</h4>\n<ol>\n  <li><strong>Rub:</strong> Coat pork with herb paste.</li>\n  <li><strong>Seal:</strong> Vacuum seal.</li>\n  <li><strong>Marinate:</strong> 20 mins room temp or freeze.</li>\n</ol>\n<h4>Cooking:</h4>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Sear:</strong> Brown all sides.</li>\n  <li><strong>Roast:</strong> 400F (200C) for 15-20 mins (145F internal).</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>COMPONENT 2: Apple Cider Chutney</h3>\n<h4>Ingredients:</h4>\n<ul>\n  <li>Apples, onion, cider vinegar, sugar, spices</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Instructions:</h4>\n<ol>\n  <li><strong>Cook:</strong> Simmer until thick. Cool.</li>\n  <li><strong>Seal:</strong> Portion and seal.</li>\n  <li><strong>Store:</strong> Fridge 2 weeks or freeze.</li>\n</ol>\n<h3>COMPONENT 3: Roasted Brussels Sprouts</h3>\n<h4>Ingredients:</h4>\n<ul>\n  <li>Brussels sprouts, halved</li>\n  <li>Bacon bits (cooked)</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Instructions:</h4>\n<ol>\n  <li><strong>Blanch:</strong> 3 mins boiling water. Ice bath. Dry.</li>\n  <li><strong>Seal:</strong> Vacuum seal with bacon.</li>\n  <li><strong>Cook:</strong> Roast from frozen 400F 20 mins.</li>\n</ol>\n<h3>COMPONENT 4: Sweet Potato Mash</h3>\n<h4>Instructions:</h4>\n<ol>\n  <li>Cook sweet potatoes. Mash with butter/cinnamon. Cool.</li>\n  <li>Seal flat.</li>\n  <li><strong>Reheat:</strong> Microwave.</li>\n</ol>\n<h3>COMPLETE MEAL ASSEMBLY</h3>\n<h4>Timing:</h4>\n<ul>\n  <li>5:30 PM: Preheat oven</li>\n  <li>5:40 PM: Roast pork and sprouts (same oven)</li>\n  <li>5:55 PM: Reheat mash/chutney</li>\n  <li>6:00 PM: Rest pork, serve</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Nutrition:</strong> ~450 calories, 35g protein, 15g fat, 40g carbs</p>\n"
