        "content": "<p><strong>Difficulty:</strong> Easy | <strong>Servings:</strong> 4-6 servings (16-20 koftas)</p>\n<h3>Time Requirements</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Prep Time:</strong> 20 minutes</li>\n  <li><strong>Marination Time:</strong> N/A (flavors meld in storage)</li>\n  <li><strong>Cook Time:</strong> 10-12 minutes</li>\n  <li><strong>Total Time:</strong> 30 minutes active</li>\n  <li><strong>Storage Duration:</strong> 2-3 years frozen</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Ingredients</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>1 kg (2.2 lbs) ground beef (80/20 or 85/15)</li>\n  <li>1 large onion, grated and squeezed dry (approx. 150g / 5 oz)</li>\n  <li>4 cloves garlic, minced</li>\n  <li>30g (Â½ cup) fresh parsley, finely chopped</li>\n  <li>10g (2 tsp) ground cumin</li>\n  <li>10g (2 tsp) ground coriander</li>\n  <li>10g (2 tsp) paprika (sweet or smoked)</li>\n  <li>2g (Â½ tsp) baking soda (helps texture)</li>\n  <li>10g (2 tsp) salt</li>\n  <li>5g (1 tsp) black pepper</li>\n  <li>30g (Â¼ cup) breadcrumbs (optional binder)</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Optional Additions:</h4>\n<ul>\n  <li>1 tsp red pepper flakes for heat</li>\n  <li>1 tsp sumac for tanginess</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Equipment Needed</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>Vacuum sealer</li>\n  <li>Vacuum sealer bags (quart/liter size)</li>\n  <li>Large mixing bowl</li>\n  <li>Grater (for onion)</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Step-by-Step Instructions</h3>\n<h4>PREPARATION:</h4>\n<ol>\n  <li><strong>Prepare Aromatics:</strong> Grate the onion and squeeze out excess moisture using a paper towel or cheesecloth. This prevents the mixture from becoming too wet. Finely chop the parsley and mince the garlic.</li>\n  <li><strong>Mix Ingredients:</strong> In a large bowl, combine the ground beef, prepared onion, garlic, parsley, cumin, coriander, paprika, baking soda, salt, pepper, and breadcrumbs (if using).</li>\n  <li><strong>Knead the Meat:</strong> Knead the mixture vigorously with your hands for 3-5 minutes. This is crucial! It releases proteins (myosin) that help the koftas hold their shape and gives them that characteristic springy texture.</li>\n</ol>\n<h4>VACUUM SEALING:</h4>\n<ol>\n  <li><strong>Portioning:</strong></li>\n</ol>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Option A (Ready-to-Cook):</strong> Form mixture into oval shapes (koftas) or patties. Place on a parchment-lined tray and freeze for 1-2 hours until solid (flash freezing). Then transfer to vacuum bags.</li>\n  <li><strong>Option B (Bulk Mix):</strong> Divide the bulk mixture into meal-sized portions (e.g., 500g/1 lb bags). Flatten the bags for easy storage and quick thawing.</li>\n</ul>\n<ol>\n  <li><strong>Sealing:</strong></li>\n</ol>\n<ul>\n  <li>Place portions in vacuum bags.</li>\n  <li>If flash-frozen (Option A), seal normally.</li>\n  <li>If bulk mix (Option B), flatten the bag to about 1-inch thickness.</li>\n  <li>Vacuum and seal.</li>\n  <li>Label with date and recipe name.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>STORAGE:</h4>\n<ol>\n  <li>Store flat in the freezer.</li>\n</ol>\n<h4>COOKING FROM FROZEN/THAWED:</h4>\n<ol>\n  <li><strong>Thawing:</strong> Thaw in the refrigerator overnight. If in a flat pack, it will thaw quickly (in cold water in ~30 mins).</li>\n  <li><strong>Cooking:</strong></li>\n</ol>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Grill/Pan:</strong> Cook on medium-high heat for 4-5 minutes per side until browned and cooked through (Internal temp 160Â°F/71Â°C).</li>\n  <li><strong>Oven:</strong> Bake at 400Â°F (200Â°C) for 15-20 minutes.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Storage Instructions</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Freezer:</strong> 2-3 years</li>\n  <li><strong>Refrigerator:</strong> 24 hours after thawing</li>\n  <li><strong>After Opening:</strong> Cook immediately</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Pro Tips (Vacuum Sealing Advantages)</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Flavor Infusion:</strong> The spices penetrate the meat deeply during storage, resulting in a more flavorful kofta than fresh.</li>\n  <li><strong>Texture:</strong> The vacuum compression helps the meat bind, improving the texture.</li>\n  <li><strong>Convenience:</strong> Having pre-seasoned meat ready to shape or cook saves massive prep time on weeknights.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Variations</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Spicy Kofta:</strong> Add 1 tbsp harissa paste or more chili flakes.</li>\n  <li><strong>Herbed Kofta:</strong> Add fresh mint and dill along with parsley.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Nutrition Information (Per Serving - approx 150g)</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>Calories: ~350</li>\n  <li>Protein: ~26g</li>\n  <li>Fat: ~25g</li>\n  <li>Carbs: ~5g</li>\n</ul>\n"
