        "content": "<p><strong>Difficulty:</strong> Easy | <strong>Servings:</strong> 6-8 servings</p>\n<h3>Time Requirements</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Prep Time:</strong> 10 minutes</li>\n  <li><strong>Marination Time:</strong> N/A</li>\n  <li><strong>Cook Time:</strong> 20 minutes</li>\n  <li><strong>Total Time:</strong> 30 minutes + cooling time</li>\n  <li><strong>Storage Duration:</strong> 6-12 months frozen</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Ingredients</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>1.5 kg (3.3 lbs) ground beef</li>\n  <li>2 large onions, diced</li>\n  <li>4 cloves garlic, minced</li>\n  <li>45g (3 tbsp) chili powder</li>\n  <li>15g (1 tbsp) ground cumin</li>\n  <li>5g (1 tsp) dried oregano</li>\n  <li>5g (1 tsp) paprika</li>\n  <li>2g (Â½ tsp) cayenne pepper (optional)</li>\n  <li>15g (1 tbsp) salt</li>\n  <li>250ml (1 cup) beef broth or water</li>\n  <li>15ml (1 tbsp) tomato paste</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Optional Additions:</h4>\n<ul>\n  <li>Diced bell peppers</li>\n  <li>Black beans or corn (add at end)</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Equipment Needed</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>Vacuum sealer</li>\n  <li>Vacuum sealer bags (pint/quart size)</li>\n  <li>Large skillet or pot</li>\n  <li>Spatula</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Step-by-Step Instructions</h3>\n<h4>PREPARATION:</h4>\n<ol>\n  <li><strong>Brown Beef:</strong> In a large skillet over medium-high heat, brown the ground beef, breaking it up into crumbles. Cook until no longer pink. Drain excess fat if desired.</li>\n  <li><strong>Add Aromatics:</strong> Add diced onions and cook for 5 minutes until softened. Add garlic and cook for 1 minute.</li>\n  <li><strong>Season:</strong> Stir in chili powder, cumin, oregano, paprika, cayenne, salt, and tomato paste. Cook for 1 minute to toast spices.</li>\n  <li><strong>Simmer:</strong> Add broth/water. Simmer for 5-10 minutes until liquid reduces and meat is coated in a thick sauce.</li>\n  <li><strong>Cool:</strong> <strong>CRITICAL STEP.</strong> Spread meat on a baking sheet to cool completely to room temperature. Vacuum sealing hot food is dangerous and can ruin the machine.</li>\n</ol>\n<h4>VACUUM SEALING:</h4>\n<ol>\n  <li><strong>Portion:</strong> Divide cooled meat into meal-sized portions (e.g., 2 cups per bag).</li>\n  <li><strong>Bagging:</strong> Fill vacuum bags, keeping the seal area clean.</li>\n  <li><strong>Sealing:</strong></li>\n</ol>\n<ul>\n  <li>Use the <strong>PULSE</strong> setting if your machine has it, as there may be some moisture.</li>\n  <li>Watch the liquid line carefully. Stop vacuum before liquid enters the sealer.</li>\n  <li>Seal double for safety.</li>\n  <li>Flatten the bags for efficient storage.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>STORAGE:</h4>\n<ol>\n  <li>Store flat in the freezer.</li>\n</ol>\n<h4>COOKING FROM FROZEN/THAWED:</h4>\n<ol>\n  <li><strong>Reheating:</strong></li>\n</ol>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Microwave:</strong> Empty into bowl, cover, heat 2-3 mins.</li>\n  <li><strong>Stove:</strong> Empty into saucepan, add splash of water, heat on medium.</li>\n  <li><strong>Boil-in-Bag:</strong> If using suitable bags, simmer the sealed bag in water for 10-15 mins.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Storage Instructions</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Freezer:</strong> 6-12 months</li>\n  <li><strong>Refrigerator:</strong> 3-4 days</li>\n  <li><strong>After Opening:</strong> Eat within 3 days</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Pro Tips (Vacuum Sealing Advantages)</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Instant Meal:</strong> Tacos, nachos, or taco salads ready in 5 minutes.</li>\n  <li><strong>Batch Efficiency:</strong> Cook 3lbs at once instead of 1lb three times.</li>\n  <li><strong>Portion Control:</strong> Freeze in exact family-size portions.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Variations</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Turkey Taco Meat:</strong> Swap beef for ground turkey (add a little oil).</li>\n  <li><strong>Hidden Veggie:</strong> Add finely grated carrots or zucchini during cooking.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Nutrition Information (Per Serving)</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>Calories: ~300</li>\n  <li>Protein: ~22g</li>\n  <li>Fat: ~20g</li>\n  <li>Carbs: ~6g</li>\n</ul>\n"
