        "description": "Vacuum-sealing lemon-oregano marinade into pork creates authentic Greek souvlaki flavor in 30 minutes instead of overnight. The acid from lemon and yogurt breaks down proteins rapidly under vacuum pressure, resulting in tender, juicy skewers with deep Mediterranean flavor. These can be frozen on skewers and grilled directly from frozenâ€”perfect for quick summer meals.",
        "prepTime": "20 minutes",
        "cookTime": "10-12 minutes",
        "totalTime": "60 minutes",
        "content": "<p><strong>Difficulty:</strong> Easy</p>\n<p><strong>Servings:</strong> 6 (12 skewers)</p>\n<h3>Time Requirements</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Prep Time:</strong> 20 minutes</li>\n  <li><strong>Marination Time:</strong> 30 minutes (vacuum) or 6 hours (traditional)</li>\n  <li><strong>Cook Time:</strong> 10-12 minutes</li>\n  <li><strong>Total Time:</strong> 60 minutes</li>\n  <li><strong>Storage Duration:</strong> Frozen 12-18 months</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Why This Meal is Special</h3>\n<p>Vacuum-sealing lemon-oregano marinade into pork creates authentic Greek souvlaki flavor in 30 minutes instead of overnight. The acid from lemon and yogurt breaks down proteins rapidly under vacuum pressure, resulting in tender, juicy skewers with deep Mediterranean flavor. These can be frozen on skewers and grilled directly from frozenâ€”perfect for quick summer meals.</p>\n<h3>Ingredients</h3>\n<h4>For the Marinade:</h4>\n<ul>\n  <li>1 kg pork tenderloin or pork shoulder, cut into 3cm cubes (2.2 lbs)</li>\n  <li>120ml Greek yogurt (1/2 cup)</li>\n  <li>60ml olive oil (1/4 cup)</li>\n  <li>2 lemons, juiced (80ml / 1/3 cup)</li>\n  <li>4 cloves garlic, minced (20g / 0.7 oz)</li>\n  <li>2 tbsp dried oregano (30g)</li>\n  <li>1 tsp paprika (5g)</li>\n  <li>1 tsp salt (5g)</li>\n  <li>1/2 tsp black pepper (2.5g)</li>\n  <li>1/2 tsp cumin (2.5g)</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>For Skewers:</h4>\n<ul>\n  <li>Wooden or metal skewers</li>\n  <li>2 red onions, cut into chunks (300g / 10.5 oz)</li>\n  <li>2 bell peppers, cut into 3cm squares (300g / 10.5 oz)</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Equipment</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>Vacuum sealer</li>\n  <li>Vacuum sealer bags (gallon size)</li>\n  <li>12 skewers (soak wooden skewers in water for 30 min)</li>\n  <li>Grill, grill pan, or broiler</li>\n  <li>Tongs</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Instructions</h3>\n<h4>Preparation:</h4>\n<ol>\n  <li>Cut pork into 3cm (1.2 inch) cubesâ€”uniform size ensures even cooking.</li>\n  <li>In a bowl, whisk together Greek yogurt, olive oil, lemon juice, garlic, oregano, paprika, salt, pepper, and cumin.</li>\n</ol>\n<h4>Vacuum Marination:</h4>\n<ol>\n  <li>Place pork cubes into a vacuum sealer bag.</li>\n  <li>Pour marinade over pork, ensuring all pieces are coated.</li>\n  <li>Vacuum seal on <strong>gentle setting</strong> (pulse mode).</li>\n  <li>Massage bag to distribute marinade evenly.</li>\n  <li>Refrigerate for <strong>30 minutes minimum</strong>. The lemon acid + vacuum pressure will tenderize the pork rapidly.</li>\n</ol>\n<h4>Skewering:</h4>\n<ol>\n  <li>Remove pork from vacuum bag (discard marinadeâ€”it contains raw meat juice).</li>\n  <li>Thread pork onto skewers, alternating with onion chunks and bell pepper squares.</li>\n  <li>Leave small gaps between pieces for even cooking.</li>\n</ol>\n<h4>Grilling:</h4>\n<ol>\n  <li>Preheat grill to medium-high heat (or broiler).</li>\n  <li>Oil the grill grates.</li>\n  <li>Grill skewers for 10-12 minutes, turning every 3 minutes, until pork reaches 63Â°C (145Â°F) internal temp.</li>\n  <li>Pork should have nice char marks but remain juicy inside.</li>\n</ol>\n<h4>Serving:</h4>\n<ol>\n  <li>Rest for 2-3 minutes.</li>\n  <li>Serve with pita bread, tzatziki sauce, and Greek salad.</li>\n</ol>\n<h4>For Freezing (Pre-Skewered):</h4>\n<ol>\n  <li>After skewering raw marinated pork, place skewers on a parchment-lined tray.</li>\n  <li>Flash-freeze for 2 hours until solid.</li>\n  <li>Transfer frozen skewers to vacuum sealer bags (or wrap tightly in plastic wrap then vacuum seal).</li>\n  <li>Freeze flat.</li>\n  <li>To cook from frozen: Grill directly from frozen, adding 5-7 minutes to cook time.</li>\n</ol>\n<h4>For Freezing (Cooked):</h4>\n<ol>\n  <li>Cool grilled skewers completely.</li>\n  <li>Vacuum seal in portions.</li>\n  <li>Reheat in oven at 180Â°C (350Â°F) for 10-12 minutes.</li>\n</ol>\n<h3>Storage</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Frozen (raw marinated, skewered):</strong> 12-18 months</li>\n  <li><strong>Frozen (cooked):</strong> 8-10 months</li>\n  <li><strong>Refrigerated (marinated raw):</strong> 2-3 days</li>\n  <li><strong>Refrigerated (cooked):</strong> 4-5 days</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Pro Tips</h3>\n<h4>Vacuum Advantage:</h4>\n<ul>\n  <li>Lemon acid + vacuum = ultra-tender pork in 30 minutes.</li>\n  <li>Yogurt enzymes penetrate deeply, creating restaurant-quality texture.</li>\n  <li>Pre-skewered frozen portions = grab-and-grill convenience.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Cooking Tips:</h4>\n<ul>\n  <li>Don't overcrowd skewersâ€”leave gaps for heat circulation.</li>\n  <li>Oil the grill grates well to prevent sticking.</li>\n  <li>For extra char, brush with olive oil before grilling.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Serving Suggestions:</h4>\n<ul>\n  <li>Pita wraps with tzatziki, tomatoes, and red onion</li>\n  <li>Greek rice pilaf and Greek salad</li>\n  <li>Orzo pasta salad</li>\n  <li>Hummus and roasted vegetables</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Variations:</h4>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Spicy Version:</strong> Add 1 tsp chili flakes or 1 diced jalapeÃ±o to marinade.</li>\n  <li><strong>Herb Version:</strong> Add fresh mint and parsley to marinade.</li>\n  <li><strong>Lamb Souvlaki:</strong> Substitute lamb shoulder for pork (same method).</li>\n</ul>\n"
