        "content": "<p><strong>Difficulty:</strong> Easy | <strong>Servings/Yield:</strong> 4 bags (2 servings each)</p>\n<h3>Time Requirements</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Prep Time:</strong> 20 minutes</li>\n  <li><strong>Cook Time:</strong> 2-3 minutes (blanching)</li>\n  <li><strong>Total Time:</strong> 45 minutes (including cooling/drying)</li>\n  <li><strong>Storage Duration:</strong> 12-18 months</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Ingredients</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>500g (1.1 lbs) broccoli florets</li>\n  <li>300g (10.5 oz) carrots, sliced diagonally</li>\n  <li>300g (10.5 oz) bell peppers (red/yellow), sliced</li>\n  <li>200g (7 oz) snap peas or snow peas, trimmed</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Equipment Needed</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>Vacuum sealer</li>\n  <li>Vacuum sealer bags (quart/liter size)</li>\n  <li>Large stockpot (for boiling water)</li>\n  <li>Large bowl (for ice bath)</li>\n  <li>Salad spinner or clean kitchen towels</li>\n  <li>Baking sheet (for flash freezing optional)</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Step-by-Step Instructions</h3>\n<h4>PREPARATION:</h4>\n<ol>\n  <li>Wash all vegetables thoroughly.</li>\n  <li>Cut broccoli into uniform bite-sized florets.</li>\n  <li>Peel and slice carrots into thin diagonal coins (approx 1/8 inch thick).</li>\n  <li>Slice peppers into strips.</li>\n  <li>Trim ends of snap peas.</li>\n</ol>\n<h4>COOKING (Blanching):</h4>\n<ol>\n  <li>Bring a large pot of water to a rolling boil. Add 1 tbsp salt.</li>\n  <li>Prepare a large bowl with ice and cold water.</li>\n  <li>Blanch vegetables in batches (don't crowd the pot):</li>\n</ol>\n<ul>\n  <li>Carrots: 3 minutes</li>\n  <li>Broccoli: 2 minutes</li>\n  <li>Peppers & Snap Peas: 1.5 minutes</li>\n</ul>\n<ol>\n  <li>Immediately transfer boiled vegetables to the ice bath using a slotted spoon.</li>\n  <li>Let sit in ice water for the same amount of time they boiled to stop cooking completely.</li>\n</ol>\n<h4>COOLING & DRYING:</h4>\n<ol>\n  <li>Drain vegetables well.</li>\n  <li><strong>CRITICAL:</strong> Dry thoroughly. Use a salad spinner or lay out on kitchen towels for 15-20 minutes. Excess moisture causes ice crystals.</li>\n</ol>\n<h4>VACUUM SEALING:</h4>\n<ol>\n  <li>Mix vegetables together for a colorful blend, or keep separate if preferred.</li>\n  <li>Portion into vacuum bags (approx 300-350g per bag).</li>\n  <li>Arrange in a single flat layer.</li>\n  <li>Vacuum seal using <strong>Normal</strong> setting. If vegetables are delicate, use <strong>Pulse</strong> to avoid crushing.</li>\n  <li>Label: \"Stir-Fry Mix, [Date], Best by [Date + 18 months]\".</li>\n</ol>\n<h4>STORAGE:</h4>\n<ol>\n  <li>Freeze flat. Once frozen, can be stored vertically.</li>\n</ol>\n<h4>REHEATING/COOKING:</h4>\n<ol>\n  <li>Do not thaw. Cook directly from frozen.</li>\n  <li>Stir-fry in hot oil for 3-4 minutes until heated through.</li>\n</ol>\n<h3>Storage Instructions</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Freezer:</strong> 12-18 months</li>\n  <li><strong>Refrigerator:</strong> Not recommended (blanched veggies degrade faster in fridge)</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Pro Tips</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Blanching is Non-Negotiable:</strong> It deactivates enzymes that cause flavor/color loss and spoilage.</li>\n  <li><strong>Dryness = Quality:</strong> The drier the veggies before sealing, the less frost you'll see in the bag.</li>\n  <li><strong>Portion Control:</strong> Pack in amounts you will actually use for one meal.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Pairs Well With</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>T3-019 Teriyaki Glaze</li>\n  <li>T3-026 Marinated Salmon Fillets</li>\n  <li>T3-028 Ready-to-Cook Shrimp</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Nutrition Information (Per Serving)</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>Calories: ~45</li>\n  <li>Carbs: 9g</li>\n  <li>Protein: 2g</li>\n  <li>Fiber: 3g</li>\n</ul>\n"
