        "content": "<p><strong>Difficulty:</strong> Easy | <strong>Servings/Yield:</strong> 4 bags (2 servings each)</p>\n<h3>Time Requirements</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Prep Time:</strong> 15 minutes</li>\n  <li><strong>Cook Time:</strong> 3 minutes</li>\n  <li><strong>Total Time:</strong> 40 minutes</li>\n  <li><strong>Storage Duration:</strong> 12-18 months</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Ingredients</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>1kg (2.2 lbs) fresh green beans</li>\n  <li>1 tbsp sea salt (for blanching water)</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Equipment Needed</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>Vacuum sealer</li>\n  <li>Vacuum sealer bags</li>\n  <li>Large pot</li>\n  <li>Ice bath bowl</li>\n  <li>Towels for drying</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Step-by-Step Instructions</h3>\n<h4>PREPARATION:</h4>\n<ol>\n  <li>Wash beans in cold water.</li>\n  <li>Trim the stem ends (snip or cut). Leave tails if desired for rustic look.</li>\n</ol>\n<h4>COOKING (Blanching):</h4>\n<ol>\n  <li>Boil salted water.</li>\n  <li>Add beans in batches.</li>\n  <li>Blanch for exactly 3 minutes (beans should be bright green and crisp-tender).</li>\n  <li>Plunge immediately into ice bath for 3 minutes.</li>\n</ol>\n<h4>COOLING & DRYING:</h4>\n<ol>\n  <li>Drain well.</li>\n  <li>Spread on towels and pat dry. Ensure no water droplets remain.</li>\n</ol>\n<h4>VACUUM SEALING:</h4>\n<ol>\n  <li>Portion into bags (approx 250g per bag).</li>\n  <li>Arrange beans parallel to each other for a neat, flat pack.</li>\n  <li>Vacuum seal on <strong>Normal</strong> setting.</li>\n  <li>Label: \"Green Beans, [Date], 18 months\".</li>\n</ol>\n<h4>STORAGE:</h4>\n<ol>\n  <li>Store flat in freezer.</li>\n</ol>\n<h4>REHEATING/COOKING:</h4>\n<ol>\n  <li>Steam from frozen (3-4 minutes).</li>\n  <li>Or sautÃ© with butter and garlic (5-6 minutes).</li>\n</ol>\n<h3>Storage Instructions</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Freezer:</strong> 12-18 months</li>\n  <li><strong>Refrigerator:</strong> 3-5 days (if seal is broken)</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Pro Tips</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Texture:</strong> Blanching preserves the \"snap\". Unblanched frozen beans get mushy.</li>\n  <li><strong>Seasoning:</strong> Do not salt before freezing; salt draws out moisture. Season when cooking.</li>\n  <li><strong>Organization:</strong> Parallel packing saves space and prevents beans from snapping.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Pairs Well With</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>T3-023 Marinated Pork Chops</li>\n  <li>T3-011 Mashed Potatoes</li>\n  <li>T3-017 Garlic Herb Compound Butter</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Nutrition Information (Per Serving)</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>Calories: ~35</li>\n  <li>Carbs: 7g</li>\n  <li>Protein: 2g</li>\n</ul>\n"
