        "content": "<p><strong>Difficulty:</strong> Easy | <strong>Servings/Yield:</strong> 4 bags</p>\n<h3>Time Requirements</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Prep Time:</strong> 15 minutes</li>\n  <li><strong>Marination:</strong> 15 mins (vacuum)</li>\n  <li><strong>Total Time:</strong> 30 minutes</li>\n  <li><strong>Storage Duration:</strong> 8-12 months</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Ingredients</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>2 medium zucchini, sliced into planks or rounds</li>\n  <li>1 large eggplant, sliced into rounds</li>\n  <li>2 red bell peppers, quartered</li>\n  <li>1 red onion, cut into wedges (keep root intact)</li>\n  <li><strong>Marinade:</strong></li>\n  <li>60ml (1/4 cup) olive oil</li>\n  <li>30ml (2 tbsp) balsamic vinegar</li>\n  <li>2 cloves garlic, minced (cooked/paste preferred for safety, or powder)</li>\n  <li>1 tsp dried oregano</li>\n  <li>1/2 tsp salt</li>\n  <li>1/4 tsp black pepper</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Equipment Needed</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>Vacuum sealer</li>\n  <li>Vacuum sealer bags</li>\n  <li>Mixing bowl</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Step-by-Step Instructions</h3>\n<h4>PREPARATION:</h4>\n<ol>\n  <li>Slice all vegetables to uniform thickness (approx 1/2 inch) for even cooking.</li>\n  <li>Whisk marinade ingredients in a small bowl.</li>\n</ol>\n<h4>VACUUM SEALING:</h4>\n<ol>\n  <li>Toss vegetables with marinade to coat evenly.</li>\n  <li>Place in vacuum bags in a single layer. Do not overfill.</li>\n  <li><strong>CRITICAL:</strong> Use <strong>Pulse</strong> mode or <strong>Moist</strong> setting. Stop vacuum before liquid is drawn into the sealer.</li>\n  <li>Seal immediately.</li>\n  <li>Label: \"Grilling Veggies, [Date], 12 months\".</li>\n</ol>\n<h4>STORAGE:</h4>\n<ol>\n  <li>Freeze flat.</li>\n</ol>\n<h4>REHEATING/COOKING:</h4>\n<ol>\n  <li>Thaw in refrigerator overnight or in cold water.</li>\n  <li>Grill over medium-high heat until charred and tender (3-4 mins per side).</li>\n  <li>Or roast at 400Â°F (200Â°C) for 20 minutes.</li>\n</ol>\n<h3>Storage Instructions</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Freezer:</strong> 8-12 months</li>\n  <li><strong>Refrigerator:</strong> 3-4 days (marinating)</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Pro Tips</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Sponge Effect:</strong> Eggplant and zucchini absorb marinade rapidly under vacuum.</li>\n  <li><strong>Oil Safety:</strong> If using raw garlic, freeze IMMEDIATELY to prevent botulism risk. For fridge storage, use garlic powder.</li>\n  <li><strong>Grill Ready:</strong> These are perfect for camping or quick BBQ dinners.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Pairs Well With</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>T3-023 Marinated Pork Chops</li>\n  <li>T3-030 Naan Bread</li>\n  <li>T3-021 Pre-Cooked Kidney Beans</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Nutrition Information (Per Serving)</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>Calories: ~90</li>\n  <li>Fat: 7g</li>\n  <li>Carbs: 8g</li>\n</ul>\n"
