        "content": "<p><strong>Difficulty:</strong> Easy | <strong>Servings/Yield:</strong> 4 bags</p>\n<h3>Time Requirements</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Prep Time:</strong> 15 minutes</li>\n  <li><strong>Cook Time:</strong> 3-4 minutes (par-boil)</li>\n  <li><strong>Total Time:</strong> 45 minutes</li>\n  <li><strong>Storage Duration:</strong> 10-12 months</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Ingredients</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>1.5kg (3.3 lbs) russet or yukon gold potatoes</li>\n  <li>3 tbsp olive oil</li>\n  <li>2 tsp paprika</li>\n  <li>1 tsp garlic powder</li>\n  <li>1 tsp onion powder</li>\n  <li>1 tsp dried thyme</li>\n  <li>1 tsp salt</li>\n  <li>1/2 tsp black pepper</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Equipment Needed</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>Vacuum sealer</li>\n  <li>Vacuum bags</li>\n  <li>Pot for boiling</li>\n  <li>Baking sheet (for flash freezing)</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Step-by-Step Instructions</h3>\n<h4>PREPARATION:</h4>\n<ol>\n  <li>Scrub potatoes (peel if desired, but skin-on is better for wedges).</li>\n  <li>Cut into uniform wedges (8-10 wedges per potato).</li>\n</ol>\n<h4>COOKING (Par-boil):</h4>\n<ol>\n  <li>Place wedges in boiling water for 3-4 minutes. They should be slightly softened on the outside but raw in the middle.</li>\n  <li>Drain and let steam dry for 5 minutes. This roughens the edges for crispiness.</li>\n</ol>\n<h4>COOLING & SEASONING:</h4>\n<ol>\n  <li>Toss warm potatoes with oil and spices.</li>\n  <li>Let cool completely to room temperature.</li>\n</ol>\n<h4>VACUUM SEALING:</h4>\n<ol>\n  <li><strong>Optional but Recommended:</strong> Flash freeze on a baking sheet for 1 hour before sealing to prevent squishing.</li>\n  <li>Place in vacuum bags.</li>\n  <li>Seal on <strong>Normal</strong> setting (if frozen) or <strong>Gentle</strong> (if soft).</li>\n  <li>Label: \"Potato Wedges, [Date], 12 months\".</li>\n</ol>\n<h4>STORAGE:</h4>\n<ol>\n  <li>Freeze flat.</li>\n</ol>\n<h4>REHEATING/COOKING:</h4>\n<ol>\n  <li>Cook from frozen.</li>\n  <li>Air Fry: 400Â°F (200Â°C) for 15-18 minutes.</li>\n  <li>Oven: 425Â°F (220Â°C) for 20-25 minutes, flipping halfway.</li>\n</ol>\n<h3>Storage Instructions</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Freezer:</strong> 10-12 months</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Pro Tips</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Par-boiling:</strong> Removes excess starch and ensures the inside is fluffy while the outside gets crispy.</li>\n  <li><strong>Oil Coating:</strong> The oil helps the spices stick and aids in crisping upon reheating.</li>\n  <li><strong>Don't Overcrowd:</strong> Pack in single layers for best shape retention.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Pairs Well With</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>T3-001 Seasoned Smash Burger (Tier 1)</li>\n  <li>T3-026 Marinated Salmon Fillets</li>\n  <li>T3-025 Breakfast Sausage Patties</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Nutrition Information (Per Serving)</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>Calories: ~180</li>\n  <li>Carbs: 30g</li>\n  <li>Fat: 5g</li>\n</ul>\n"
