        "content": "<p><strong>Difficulty:</strong> Easy | <strong>Servings/Yield:</strong> 4 bags (2 cups each)</p>\n<h3>Time Requirements</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Prep Time:</strong> 5 minutes</li>\n  <li><strong>Cook Time:</strong> 20 minutes</li>\n  <li><strong>Total Time:</strong> 45 minutes (including cooling)</li>\n  <li><strong>Storage Duration:</strong> 6-12 months</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Ingredients</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>4 cups uncooked white rice (jasmine, basmati, or long grain)</li>\n  <li>6 cups water (or ratio per package instructions)</li>\n  <li>1 tsp salt</li>\n  <li>2 tbsp oil (prevents sticking)</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Equipment Needed</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>Vacuum sealer</li>\n  <li>Vacuum bags</li>\n  <li>Rice cooker or pot</li>\n  <li>Baking sheet (for cooling)</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Step-by-Step Instructions</h3>\n<h4>PREPARATION:</h4>\n<ol>\n  <li>Rinse rice thoroughly until water runs clear.</li>\n</ol>\n<h4>COOKING:</h4>\n<ol>\n  <li>Cook rice according to package directions or use a rice cooker.</li>\n  <li>Once cooked, fluff with a fork.</li>\n</ol>\n<h4>COOLING:</h4>\n<ol>\n  <li><strong>CRITICAL:</strong> Spread rice onto baking sheets in a thin layer.</li>\n  <li>Drizzle with oil and toss gently to coat grains (prevents a solid brick).</li>\n  <li>Cool completely to room temperature. Warm rice = bacterial risk + mushy texture.</li>\n</ol>\n<h4>VACUUM SEALING:</h4>\n<ol>\n  <li>Portion into bags (approx 2 cups cooked rice per bag).</li>\n  <li>Flatten the bag so the rice is in a thin \"sheet\" (approx 1/2 inch thick).</li>\n  <li>Vacuum seal on <strong>Normal</strong> setting.</li>\n  <li>Label: \"White Rice, [Date], 12 months\".</li>\n</ol>\n<h4>STORAGE:</h4>\n<ol>\n  <li>Freeze flat.</li>\n</ol>\n<h4>REHEATING/COOKING:</h4>\n<ol>\n  <li><strong>Microwave:</strong> Cut corner of bag, microwave 2-3 minutes. The steam stays inside and rehydrates the rice perfectly.</li>\n  <li><strong>Stir-Fry:</strong> Break up the frozen \"sheet\" into chunks and toss directly into hot wok.</li>\n</ol>\n<h3>Storage Instructions</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Freezer:</strong> 6-12 months</li>\n  <li><strong>Refrigerator:</strong> 3-4 days</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Pro Tips</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Flat Pack:</strong> Freezing in a thin sheet makes it thaw instantly and reheat evenly.</li>\n  <li><strong>Oil is Key:</strong> Don't skip the oil; it keeps grains separate.</li>\n  <li><strong>Day-Old Rice:</strong> This frozen rice is actually BETTER for fried rice than fresh rice because it's drier.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Pairs Well With</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>T3-019 Teriyaki Glaze</li>\n  <li>T3-016 Curry Sauce Base</li>\n  <li>T3-001 Seasoned Smash Burger (as a bowl)</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Nutrition Information (Per Serving)</h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>Calories: ~200</li>\n  <li>Carbs: 45g</li>\n  <li>Protein: 4g</li>\n</ul>\n"
